This paper deals with physical layer security, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of an ARQ protocol, which is related to network security (cs.NI) and cyber security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of concatenated frames, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.CR, followed by cs.CY, cs.NI, and cs.MM.
